This project began as a fork of Seafile Server
(https://github.com/haiwen/seafile-server), originally developed by
Seafile Ltd. The Go implementation, standalone runtime, SeaDrive
compatibility shims, and TUI client are new work; the file sync
protocol and on-disk format remain compatible with Seafile clients.

The Seafile name and logo are trademarks of Seafile Ltd. and are not
used by this project. "Silo" is a separate project that speaks the
Seafile sync protocol; it is not affiliated with or endorsed by
Seafile Ltd.
